general_context:
This question belongs primarily to the Quality of the Partnership and Cooperation Arrangements criterion.
The evaluator wants to understand who the organisation is and why it is a suitable applicant for the project.
In simple terms, the evaluator is asking:
"What kind of organisation are you, what do you do, and why are you relevant for this project?"
This is not intended to be a full organisational history. Instead, it should provide a concise but comprehensive overview of the organisation and explain how its mission, experience, and expertise fit the proposed project.
Many beginners simply copy the text from their organisation's website. However, the evaluator is not interested in general promotional information. They want to understand why this specific organisation belongs in this specific consortium.
A strong answer normally includes:
the type of organisation;
its mission and main fields of work;
its target groups;
its main activities;
approximate organisational size (staff, volunteers, learners where relevant);
why its expertise contributes to the objectives of the project.
